SIMPLE: pollard
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pollard
<hw>Pol"lard</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Poll</er>
the head.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A tree having its top cut off at some
height above the ground, that may throw out branches.</def>
<rj><au>Pennant.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A clipped coin; also, a counterfeit.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Camden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A fish, the
chub.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A stag that has cast its antlers.</def>
<sd>(c)</sd> <def>A hornless animal (cow or sheep).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pollard</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pollard
<hw>Pol"lard</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Pollarded</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Pollarding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To lop the tops of, as trees;
to poll; <as>as, to <ex>pollard</ex> willows</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Evelyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pollax</ent>⟦br⟧
